# ğŸ›ï¸ AI Museum Curator â€” Greek Mythology Edition

A Streamlit web application that lets users explore Greek gods, heroes, and mythic creatures through real museum artworks (MET Museum API) and AI-generated curatorial texts.

---

## ğŸ® Quick Start â€” How to Use

1. Open the **Greek Deities** tab.  
2. Select a figure from the dropdown (comprehensive list).  
3. Read the short fixed bio. Click **"Expand description with AI"** to generate a museum-style introduction.  
4. Click **"Fetch related works from MET"** to retrieve artworks related to the figure (aliases included).  
5. Go to **Works & Analysis**, click a thumbnail to select an artwork, and then click **"Generate AI Curatorial Analysis"**.  
6. To compare two works, use the **Compare** tab and enter MET Object IDs.

---

## âœ… Features

- Dropdown selection of Greek gods/heroes/creatures (no manual typing).  
- Fixed short bios + AI expansion for richer myth background.  
- Automatic MET searches using multiple aliases for better recall.  
- Thumbnail gallery of related artworks and high-resolution viewer.  
- AI-generated curator-style analysis with sections: Overview, Context, Iconography, Myth Reading, Exhibition Recommendation.  
- Two-artwork comparative analysis.  
- Course materials link to provided slides.

**Course slides (uploaded)**: `/mnt/data/LN_-_Art_and_Advanced_Big_Data_-_W12_-_Designing_%26_Implementing_with_AI (1).pdf`

